  "text": "There are several theories that contextualize learning during debriefing in the debriefing literature. [CITATION_1] stressed the importance of alignments among the theory, design, use, and evaluation of any debriefing method. Similarly, [CITATION_2] emphasized research needs for clarifying learning explication-why debriefing practice boosts performance and how best to deploy the practice-by understanding how different debriefing elements influence each other and what combinations of these elements achieve the best outcomes. The findings again pointed to an alignment or interrelatedness between the themes identified in the present study. However, the evidence for this aspect was only reflective in all of the four papers, and no single theoretical approach appeared to be identified as more appropriate than another.",
